    FontColor->RGBColor[0, 0, 1]],
  "\n\n\tFor the above example the circle of curvature was easy to locate \
because it's center lies on the y-axis.  How do you locate the center if the \
point of tangency is not the origin?  To begin, we need the concepts of \
tangent and normal vectors. "
