Cell[TextData[{
  StyleBox["Recall.",
    FontWeight->"Bold",
    FontColor->RGBColor[0, 1, 0]],
  "  Two vectors are perpendicular if and only if their dot product is zero.\n\
\n\tIt is easy to verify that  ",
  Cell[BoxData[
      StyleBox[\(n\&\[RightVector]\),
        FontWeight->"Bold"]]],
  "  is perpendicular to  ",
  Cell[BoxData[
      StyleBox[\(t\&\[RightVector]\),
        FontWeight->"Bold"]]],
  "  with the calculation  \n\n",
  Cell[BoxData[
      RowBox[{
        RowBox[{
          StyleBox[\(u\&\[RightVector]\),
            FontWeight->"Bold"], ".", 
          StyleBox[\(n\&\[RightVector]\),
            FontWeight->"Bold"]}], " ", "=", 
        " ", \(\(1\/\(1 + \((\(f'\)[x])\)\^2\)\) {1, \(f'\)[
                  x]} . {\(-\(f'\)[x]\), 
                1} = \ \(\(1\/\(1 + \((\(f'\)[x])\)\^2\)\) \((\(-\(f'\)[
                      x]\) + \(f'\)[
                    x])\) = \(\(1\/\(1 + \((\(f'\)[x])\)\^2\)\) \((0)\) = \ 
              0\)\)\)}]]],
  ".  \n\nIt is also possible to have ",
  StyleBox["Mathematica",
    FontSlant->"Italic"],
