Cell[TextData[{
  StyleBox["Generalizations for 2D",
    FontWeight->"Bold",
    FontColor->RGBColor[0, 0, 1]],
  "\n\n\tIn two dimensions, a curve can be expressed with the parametric \
equations  ",
  Cell[BoxData[
      \(x = f[t]\)]],
  " and  ",
  Cell[BoxData[
      \(y = g[t]\)]],
  ".   Similarly, the formulas for the radius of curvature and center of \
curvature can be derived using limits.  At the point  ",
  Cell[BoxData[
      \(p\&\[RightVector][t]\  = {f[t], g[t]}\)]],
  "  the center and radius of the circle of convergence is \n\t\n\t\t",
  Cell[BoxData[
      \(c\&\[RightVector][
          t]\  = \ {f[
              t] + \(\(g'\)[t]\ \((\(f'\)[t]\^2 + \
\(g'\)[t]\^2)\)\)\/\(\(g'\)[t]\ \(f''\)[t] - \(f'\)[t]\ \(g''\)[t]\), \ 
          g[t] + \(\(f'\)[t]\ \((\(f'\)[t]\^2 + \
\(g'\)[t]\^2)\)\)\/\(\(f'\)[t]\ \(g''\)[t] - \(g'\)[t]\ \(f''\)[t]\)}\)]],
  "  \n\t\t\n\t\t",
  Cell[BoxData[
      \(r[
          t]\  = \ \ \((\(f'\)[t]\^2 + \
\(g'\)[t]\^2)\)\^\(3/2\)\/\(\(|\)\(\(f'\)[t]\ \(g''\)[t] - \(g'\)[t]\ \
\(f''\)[t]\)\(|\)\)\)]],
  "  \n\n",
  StyleBox["Remark.",
    FontWeight->"Bold",
    FontColor->RGBColor[0, 1, 0]],
  "  The absolute value is necessary, otherwise the formula would only work \
for a curve that is ",
  ButtonBox["positively oriented",
    ButtonData:>{
      URL[ "http://mathworld.wolfram.com/CurveOrientation.html"], None},
    ButtonStyle->"Hyperlink"],
  ". "
}], "Text"],

